8000.name: Immak Woods
8000.description:
Coming across some thick dark grass, tall, beautiful redwoods become
visible swaying in the wind. The leaves on the ground can be heard
crunching under the pressure of the scurrying woodland creatures. The
sweet succulent smell of honey drifts calmly through the atmosphere,
accompanied by the harmonic sound of chirping birds.

8002.name: The Druid Shack
8002.description:
A bearskin rug lays on the floor here, taking up a decent amount of space.
Quite a few pieces of weaponry and armor pervade the walls, hung by wooden
stakes, and polished to shiny perfection. A huge pot with a ladel rests in
the northwest part of the shack, no doubt used for brewing potions for
wary travellers that tend to pass by. There are numerous candles spread
about for convenient lighting purposes, and a lantern placed directly
above the pot.

8004.name: The path to the Grove.
8004.description:
A well-used game trail leads to the south where the trees thin out a bit
into a more even placement.

8007.name: Wandering the Grove
8007.description:
This area is covered in the tracks of various animals and the scent of
fresh green grass. Shrubbery can be seen growing all around, while roses
fight for sun. Extremely tall sunflowers also compete for space, as the
heads of the flowers follow the sun and stretch to the skies.

8020.name: Blessed Shrine of the Unicorn
8020.description:
This place seems a bit out of the ordinary. It seems to be the shrine of a
unicorn, hence the extremely large unicorn that seems to be reading out of
a book on the ground. Straight down the center of the shrine, there is a
flat-topped tombstone that reads "Here lies knowledge, mother nature's
medicine". A large tome that reads "The Tome of Knowledge" sits propped up
on the tombstone. On either side of the tombstone lies shelves full of
books. Grass pervades the ground, clearly being the food that feeds the
knowledgeable unicorn.

exdescs.tombstone: A large tombstone is here decaying over time.

heads of the flowers follow the sun and stretch to the skies. To the south
there is a tall unicorn hovering over a book. There is also a tall
tombstone with a large book on top of it.

8034.name: Wandering the Grove
8034.description:
Doe tracks are scattered all over the ground here. A pile of sticks bunched
up block off the exits south and west. To the east, the back of a
bookshelf is barely visible, along with the flattened top of a tombstone.
The sweet smell of honey wafts in from the north, joined by the sound of
buzzing bees doing what looks like a ritual around a pear tree.

8078.name: Well Ridden Path
8078.description:
Coming across some thick dark grass, tall, beautiful redwoods become
visible swaying in the wind. The leaves on the ground can be heard
crunching under the pressure of the scurrying woodland creatures. The
sweet succulent smell of honey drifts calmly through the atmosphere,
accompanied by the harmonic sound of chirping birds. The ground is covered
in hoofprints that appear to become more clustered together to the north.

8079.name: Well Ridden Path
8079.description:
The path is packed down hard here and covered in wagon tracks and hoof
prints from a multitude of travellers. To the west, smoke can be seen from
a set of campfires. Loud laughter can also be heard, it would appear that
someone is camping just off the road and making no attempts to keep their
presence hidden from travelling the road.

8080.name: Well Ridden Path
8080.description:
The path is packed down hard here and covered in hoof prints. In the
distance to the west, campfire smoke can be seen.

8081.name: Well Ridden Path
8081.description:
The path is packed down hard here and covered in hoof prints. The forest is
neatly trimmed away from the path here.

8082.name: Well Ridden Path
8082.description:
The path is packed down hard here and covered in hoof prints. The forest is
neatly trimmed away from the path here.

8083.name: Approaching a Stable
8083.description:
The path is packed down hard here and covered in hoof prints. The forest is
neatly trimmed away from the path here. To the north a stable can be seen
selling horses to travellers.

8084.name: Outside the Stable
8084.description:
A modest stable is just north of here adjoining a small house. Smoke
billows from the chimney and it looks like a rather comfortable place.

8085.name: Inside the Stable
8085.description:
Here in the stable the floor is covered in hay, multiple enclosures hold a
variety of horses. Salt licks, saddles and various tack equipment can be
found hanging all over.

8086.name: Stables
8086.description:
This shouldn't connect to anything, it's purely a place to store animals that
can be purchased at the stablemaster.

8090.name: Bandit Camp
8090.description:
Tents and cookfires are set up here. It would appear that a rather large
encampment of bandits have set up here just off the road, hoping to catch
unwary passersby on their way along the road between Sedna and Immak.

8000.long: The Arch-Druid, Tiger Lily stands here.

8004.short: The Unicorn, Guardian of the Grove
8004.long: The Unicorn, Guardian of the Grove, stands here.

8005.long: A gray squirrel is here, chittering away.

8006.long: Erik the Stableman is here, tending to the horses.

8007.long: A raccoon is here, eyeing you warily.

8010.long: A chestnut mare with a red mane is standing here.

8020.long: A giant worker ant is here, awaiting orders.

8021.long: A giant ant drone is here, carrying food.

8022.long: A giant soldier ant is here, clicking its mandibles and ready to fight.

8023.long: Ant larvae covers the walls of this room.

8024.long: The Queen of the Colony is here, laying hundreds of eggs.

8030.long: A heavily armed bandit is here, sharpening his blades.

8099.long: Some god abandoned a newly created lastmob here.

8001.long: a potion of recall lies here.

8030.long: A wickedly curved knife lies here.

8031.long: A brigandine cuirass made of blackened iron has been left here.

8099.long: Some god dropped a newly created lastobj here.
